      "content": "thanks. it just feels like the school is acting like their way is the only way that matters and that any parent who disagrees is just wrong or \"intolerant.\" it's hard to feel like my voice as a parent is being respected if the curriculum is presented as this settled, unquestionable truth. do you think schools have an obligation to present all the different views, even if some views are controversial, rather than just picking one side?",
